70
00:03:04.310 --> 00:03:05.040
to a GPU.

71
00:03:05.040 --> 00:03:07.580
And so my discussion here
is going to carry over.

72
00:03:07.580 --> 00:03:10.880
And then once we understand
the hardware and execution

73
00:03:10.880 --> 00:03:12.680
model of the GPU,
then we're going

74
00:03:12.680 --> 00:03:15.680
to try to understand
what makes GPUs go fast

75
00:03:15.680 --> 00:03:17.510
on certain workloads,
what makes them slow.

76
00:03:17.510 --> 00:03:19.260
We're going to understand
the performance.

77
00:03:19.260 --> 00:03:20.677
And in the last
part, this is kind

78
00:03:20.677 --> 00:03:23.240
of going to be almost
